>Description:
If you use a string constant with accented characters
in MzScheme, they show up funny, even though they're
fine in DrScheme.
>How-To-Repeat:
Set language to French.
> (require (lib "check-text.ss" "version"))
> (check-version)

[Ignore the franglais that you see, that should
be fixed once all the translation is done.]

In the response, you should see:

  Tous les logiciels PLT installTs sont a jour.

The e in "installes" and the a in "a" are displayed
as Greek letters.

